description: Azrael joins Robin as the Boy Wonder shows him the ropes, and together they attempt to thwart industrial espionage at Wayne Tech.
name: Costumes

description:
Someone has thrown Gotham City into utter chaos by by stealing ... Are you ready? Everyones literacy.  Thankfully Batman and Robin are on the case. Yet While stopping the riots and looting they find they have little time to figure out how everyones ability to read has been stolen from them.
 What is a dynamic Duo to do?
name: Riot Act

description: In order to capture the rampaging Congorilla, Congo Bill may be forced to relinquish his humanity.

Crazy Jane is stranded in the bleak hell of the real world, cut off from the Doom Patrol - if indeed they ever existed. This is a 32-page, no-ads issue, presenting Grant Morrison's final Doom Patrol story and a preview of the opening story of the new Doom Patrol writer, poet and award-winning novelist Rachel Pollack.
name: The Empire of Chairs
The Blade of Vengeance!

description: The Flash continues to fight the Alchemist.  But can he convince Linda to stay in Keystone?
name: Chemistry

description: Issue Tagline: And Entropy is Unstoppable!
name: Act of Faith

description: Thrill seeking aliens start a violent conflict with angry Earthlings.
name: Low Riders in the Sky

description: Flight's End, Part 4 of 6. On the run from the U.S. government, Hawkman and Hawkwoman take refuge in the Netherworld, a community of meta-humans who live by their own set of laws...laws Hawkman tries to disrupt when he challenges the rules of "The Hunt."
name: Flight's End, Part 4: The Hunt

description: A psychotic straw man takes centre stage in Delta; elsewhere, the Four Mopeds of the Apocalypse ride again.
name: The Coming of the Four Mopeds of the Apocalypse

description: Constantine must perform a horrble surgery on the demon, to protect her from the devils retribution.
name: She's Buying A Stairway to Heaven

description:
"Funeral for a Friend" tie-in issue! Injured and devastated, the League struggles to stay together in the aftermath of Superman's death.

This is the issue just after Superman's death by Doomsday. Many of the DC Superheroes gather to mourn his death.
name: Funeral for a Friend
Red Winter Part 2 of 6: First Chill

description: The JSA and their families take a cruise to investigate the fate of Bahdnesia and encounter Pol St. Germain, Bahdnesia's sinister general manager.
name: Give Me Liberty...

description:
Following the explosive climax of the previous issue, the Legion and the rest of the survivors reflect upon past events and make their plans for an uncertain future.

The Legion and people of Earth deal with the loss of their homeworld while preparing New Earth for habitation.
name: Beginnings

description: Robin faces off with The KGBeast and loses the girl. How can this day...or night get any worse?Wait it just did with the arrival of the Ghosted Dragons and problems arise at school! Will Robin be able to handle this or is he in over his head?
name: The Beast

volume.name: Robin III: Cry of the Huntress

description: "Brief Lives" Part 5! Dream and Delirium retrace their brother Destruction's footsteps, taking them to a dance club for a meeting with the Goddess of Love, Ishtar. Plus, readers get to see a different side of Delirium, and Matthew the raven joins the crew in their search.
name: Brief Lives 5: The Things We Do to Be Loved - Her Hands Do Not Go tothe Moon - The Driving Instructor - Tiffany Watches I - White Knights and/or Pond-Scum - Are Dalmations Flowers? - Nancy Displays Her Erudition -Wham Bam Thank You Ma'am - Tiffany Watches

description: Part 1 of the 2-part 'Ernest and Jim.' Shade is brought back to Meta to help further investigate the Area of Madness...and somehow ends up in Paris of the 1920s and in the company of two of the most famous writers of the time, James Joyce and Ernest Hemingway.
name: Ernest and Jim, Part One

description: A Little Adventure...Goes a Long Way, Part 1 of 2. McCoy and Scotty wish for a little excitement...but get more than they bargained for, when they get mixed up with a fanatic cult on an unsafe ship. They discover that lending a helping hand can have its hazards, especially with hostile forces in pursuit.
name: A Little Adventure

description: Part 4 of 6. Separated from each other, the saucer and battle sections fight the Sztazzans on two fronts, while Dr. Crusher's away team makes an astounding discovery.
name: Second Chances

description: This storyline begins a series of events that will alter completely the lives of Swamp Thing and those close to him as the Sunderland Corporation unleashes..."Project Proteus"! In the face of this threat, Swamp Thing must choose between his duties as protector of the Green and his role as husband and father. Part 1 of 2.
name: Project Proteus

description: Timber Wolf's appearance in the 20th century hasn't gone unnoticed...except he's been mistaken for the Creeper. So, Jack Ryder travels to San Francisco to investigate, leading to an all-out battle between the Creeper and Timber Wolf.
Part 1 of 2. "She's the One." While putting his new ship, Pilgrim One, through its shakedown run in space, Valor runs into Lobo...and Lobo's not happy about that!
name: She's The One!

description: Is someone else actually considering putting on Wonder Woman's costume? Not if Diana has anything to say about it!
name: Once I Was a Slave

description: Marty and the Brown family are home, but Doc's still lost his memory! Will he ever remember who he is?

volume.name: Back to the Future: Forward to the Future

description: It's off to the Children's Hospital for Icestar's annual Christmas visit. And this year, he's bringing someone special with him to help him pass out presents. Get ready for surprises when Icicle dresses up as Santa's little elfin granddaughter Chrissie Claus!
There's trouble afoot in mystic Arabia when Lady Arcane and Doctor Arcane visit an old and dear friend. Plus a Dark Malice solo adventure.

Rippin 1st Issue   New York City, 3 a.m, the Vipers are riding their Motorcycles and happen upon Pitt walking the Streets at night.  They make their first mistake by taking him on.  They club, shoot and try everything they can possibly muster to subdue him, but this only enrages Pitt and cuts them apart.  Meanwhile at the same time, Timmy in Connecticut wakes from a nightmare.  His Grandpa tries to comfort him, he has lost both of his parents and is left in Grandpa's capable hands.

Elsewhere, Detective Bobbie Harris is assigned to the Subway case (Introduced in Pitt #1/2)  which will bring Pitt into their lives.

The Creed make their way to Earth and they first confront Det. Bobbie Harris. 

Issue Introduces new characters to the mix and uses them in a great plot formed by a great artist. Dale Keown
name: Fight & Flight

description: Afraid to drain his powers, Spawn gets guns. Lots and lots of guns. He then tells Tony Twist to order Overtkill to meet him at the docks. Overtkill doesn't know what's about to hit him.
name: Payback, Part 2

description: Man of War speaks to his team of Protectors, preparing them for their imminent battle against Mr. Monday and the Steel Army. He also addressed a problem with the communication gear and how they will be resolved in two days. Meanwhile, at the very same moment, Mr. Monday speaks to his elite soldiers in the Steel Army, preparing for an unavoidable battle against the Protectors. He warns them that they should keep their armor in the best of shape against their foes. After the Protector's meeting, Richard Reinhart speaks to Marcia and apologizes about making a romantic move the day before and they make their peace. Meanwhile, President O'Brien visits Philip Reinhart in the hospital and they discuss Philip's son, Richard "Night Mask" Reinhart, being on the team. Philip doesn't like that his son is on the team but realizes his son is a grown man who has to walk his path. While the team is on patrol, Night Mask comes across a group of Steel Army members destroying a post office. He tries to alert Amazing Man but the communication device is on the fritz. Amazing Man tries to tell Night Mask to wait for backup, but he never receives the message. Night Mask decides that he can't allow the Steel Army to continue their damage and jumps into a fight. He defeats one of them and gives chase to the rest, hoping to uncover their secret headquarters. Meanwhile, Amazing Man contacts Man of War, informing him that Night Mask is missing. Man of War immediately contacts several teammates to search for Night Mask. Eternal Man tries to use his magic to find Night Mask, but Ferret uses his enhanced sense of smell to track him down his own way, with Amazing Man following him. Meanwhile, Night Mask finds the Steel Army's headquarters and comes face to face with Mr. Monday. Mr. Monday informs Night Mask that their battle will be broadcast on television, and it is, with the whole city watching. While the Protectors keep searching for Night Mask, Mr. Monday televises the brutal attack on Night Mask. Mr. Monday proves to be too powerful and kills Night Mask. Night Mask's last words are an apology to his father for not being better. Ferret, Amazing Man and Air Man find Night Mask's lifeless body with a message in blood on the wall: Monday Rules.
name: Bloody Monday

description:
Arkon's on a rampage in NYC and the Avengers are there to put an end to it. But is this threat from another dimension, just like the Gatherers?

The alien world of Polemachus suffers as the energy rings that surround it and provide it with warmth and light now choke the world with their heat. Arkon and Thundra flee Polemachus with a young girl doomed to be a human sacrifice to appease the so-called gods into relieving Polemachus of this crisis. Their destructive arrival in New York puts them at odds with the Avengers until an explanation is given, and the Avengers find themselves pulled back to Polemachus along with the three fugitives to face the priests' superstitions and wrath.
name: Arkon's Asylum

description:
It’s all-out action as Cap enter the Arena of Death!

Captain America, Falcon and Diamondback go undercover at the AIM weapons expo, on a mission for Nick Fury, and get more than they bargained for.
name: The Arena

description: A young woman, tormented by cruel neighbors, has her wish for looks turned upside down. Demons invade her small town, slaughtering everyone in sight. The Darkholders, with unexpected help from Sabretooth, try to save the town's children and anyone else they can.
name: Cry N'Garai

volume.name: Darkhold: Pages from the Book of Sins

description: The battle between Nikki and Charlie goes into overdrive! The trouble is, will the winner any strength left to take on the Badoon warrior with the Captain Universe powers? Meanwhile, Major Victory and Captain America enlist the aid of Dr. Strange to reunite the Major with his fellow Guardians! And Rancor has a dramatic confrontation with Dr. Doom!
name: We Who Are About To Die Salute You

description: The Leader has been blown to smithereens! In his place, a new villain must rise! Plus, Ironclad challenges the Hulk.
name: Filling Slots

description: Moon Knight continues to fight Demogoblin within his hallucination and gives in to his demonic form in order to beat him. Once he escapes his hold, Moon Knight runs into DeZoan, and loses his truncheon to him. DeZoan flees and as Moon Knight follows, he finds that DeZoan has freed all the prisoners and they are rioting. Despite being on a very tight schedule, Moon Knight stays to help out. As the fighting ends, Moon Knight falls to the ground--his time is up. Luckily, Frenchie programmed the Angelwing to shoot through the prison roof and rescue him, taking him to Doctor Strange and Reed Richards for "surgery". They manage to extract the demo-virus, but Reed explains that the virus permanently mutated whole clusters of his cells and he has to keep his armour on for another 48hrs to hold his body together. Back at Moon Knight's Shadowkeep, Frenchie and Marc discuss DeZoan as well as Moon Knight's "Legacy Quest".
name: Death Watch

description:
1/ Wolverine & Venom - Claws And Webs 5/6 : Dream Scars (8 pages)

2/ Mirage - Of Faith And Fable (8 pages)

3/ Ghost Rider & Cloak & Dagger - And Let There Be Light 3/4 : The Bride Of Grimbat (8 pages)

4/ Andromeda - Civil Disabilities (8 pages)
name: Wolverine & Venom - Claws And Webs 5/6 : Dream Scars

description:
Morbius and Jacob work in the lab making a cure for Morbius, without testing, Morbius injects himself with the cure. He changes back into a human. Morbius is releaved.

Menawhile elsewhere, serial killer Wayne Gifford performs a demonic ritual on himself. Covered in a serpent tattoo, Wayne sits in a demonic circle and slits his throat open. Out of Wayne's body rises the Basilisk.

Menawhile Morbius walks on the street starting back his old life as a human. All of a sudden a group of gang members attack Morbius and steal his wallet. All of a sudden he changes back to a vampire.

Back at the Lab he tries the cure again but it has no effect. So Morbius goes out to feed his blood crave.

At a dinner the thugs that jumped Morbius earlier attack a girl. She is saved by Morbius and he feeds on the gang members. the girl escapes only to be mutalated by Basilisk. Morbius later taking his wallet discovers the girl's body and gets ambushe by Baskalisk.
name: Here there be Dragons

description: Frank's pursuit of a criminal ends badly when a train hits a bus full of kids. Frank becomes haunted by their memories and goes catatonic. The Kingpin takes the opportunities he can, hiding the crook Frank was chasing. Meanwhile, a corrupt orderly sees his opportunity and decides to smother Frank.

Blue Marvel attempts to strike an alliance with The Punisher. Now why would anyone do a thing like that? Still in the White Room, Quasar talks life and death with fellow Protectors. Guest-starring Thanos!
name: The White Room

description:
The Silver Surfer is in sorrow over the loss of Shalla Bal and Nova. He is met by someone asking for help. He believes he cannot help anyone and attacks the person, only to find it is his friend the Jack of Hearts. He has left Earth because his energy can no longer be contained and controlled. The Surfer knows someone that can help, but they will need to convince him.

In the prison known as the Anvil, Nebula and Geatar are planning to release their crew. The Chancellor is in the middle of interviewing his newest prisoner when the Surfer and Jack of Hearts arrive. They wish to have one of the inmates known as Torval help create some armor for Jack. Luckily, the Surfer has some information on the Chancellor he would rather not have anyone else know about and allows them to see him.

On Galactus' ship, Firelord and Air Walker are in training excercises. Air Walker is now in perfect working order. Galactus tells them he has matters he must attend to and he is not to be disturbed. In his regenitive chamber, he is secretly reviving his former herald, Morg.

As the Surfer and Jack head to Torval, the Chancellor is called for an unscheduled prisoner. That prisoner is none other than the notorious space pirate Nebula, brought in by her first officer, Geatar.
name: Prisoners

description: Slapstick's love interest is babysitting tonight...babysitting an evil manical genius. This go wrong, not the least of which is Slapstick discovers his love is dating a muscle-bound jock.
name: Sweeney Toddler

description:
Overview

Doctor Hope, an insane psychiatrist is experimenting on sick people, creating a group of killers called Mad Dogs.
name: Return to the Mad Dog Ward, Part 2: Brainstorm!

story_arc_credits.name: Return to the Mad Dog Ward

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Return to the Mad Dog Ward

description: Thor returns.
name: Final Gauntlet

description:
In the sewers, spider-Man fights the Deathspawn and saves the Father from them. He defeats the enraged Deathspawn by blasting them with high jetted water. But spider-Man has to o back in to save Hobgoblin, other victims,as well as watch out for Venom.

Meanwhile Venom sees Demogoblin torchering Hobgoblin. Doppelganger attacks Venom.

Elsewhere Ghost Rider and Blaze fight a Deathspawn. ghost Rider kills it with the penence stare. Spider-Man joins the fight against the Deathspawn. With his webbing, he sets a wall seperating him from the victims and the Deathspawn, but Spider-Man goes back for Hobgoblin.

He stops Demogoblin but is interupted by Venom. As Venom is about to go for Spider-Man, he is caught in Doppelganger's razor webbing. But he grabs him and throws Doppelganger into way of Demogoblin's sacred killing blow.

This gives Spider-Man the chance to knock Demogoblin to the ground. He pulls out a pumpkin bomb but is dragged by the deathspawn.

Venom attacks Spider-Man but is saved by Ghost Rider. While Spider-Man escapes with the wounded Hobgoblin, Ghost Rider is left to fight Venom
name: Spirts of Venom, Part 3- Enemies: A Hate Story

description:
Daniel and Barbara Ketch were attacked by gangsters and Barbara ended up wounded. Daniel dragged his sister through a junkyard to evade the gangsters before they could finish the job. There, he stumbled across a motorcycle with a glowing gas cap. Upon touching it he became Ghost Rider, spirit of vengeance! That's how it was on your world...

Plot

In this world, the gangsters found the siblings before Dan could make contact and was killed. Barbara, delirious from her wounds, touches it accidentally and becomes Ghost Rider instead. The gangsters gather around their leader, Deathwatch, assuring him the job is done when Ghost Rider blazes out on her motorcycle carrying Dan. They attack her, but she makes short work of them. She tries to kill Deathwatch, but something prevents her and he's allowed to escape. The police arrive and try to take her in, but she throws them away and rides off. Some ways off, the Rider stops and transforms back, both entities in the body confused over what's going on.

Dan's funeral doesn't make matters any easier, nor does sleep where Barb finds herself face-to-face with Ghost Rider. He explains about his powers and purpose, and tells her he needs to be dominant in the will, but Barb refuses and decides that she herself will judge what vengeance is and how to take it. Barb wakes up, dresses, cuts her finger and becomes Ghost Rider once again.

Her first victims are a couple of muggers, which she ruthlessly exacts her vengeance on. More victims fall at her hand, including Deathwatch. But with each act of vengeance, it's followed by searing pain for Ghost Rider. That pain: the tearing away of another piece of Barb's soul with her never- ending thirst for blood and vengeance.

Soon, Ghost Rider finds herself watching a fight between Hobgoblin and Spider-Man. Spidey tries to talk Gobby down, but Ghost Rider brings him to her level and beats him mercilessly. Spidey tries to stop her, but she knocks him out and allows Gobby to be killed. When Spidey revives, he decides Ghost Rider needs to be stopped and goes to see the one man who could help: Dr. Strange.

Strange tells Spidey he was expecting him, and then introduces him to John Blaze, the original Ghost Rider. Blaze tells Spidey he's come to kill Ghost Rider since he's heard of her return. Together, they formulate a plan to bring her down.

Sometime later, Deathwatch and Blackout stand in the middle of a street in the city, calling out for Ghost Rider. They soon get their wish as she attacks, looking to make sure Deathwatch's death sticks this time. She soon has Deathwatch where she wants him until Blackout hits her in the face with webbing. She's confused until Strange drops his disguise spell and reveals the two villains to really be Spidey and Blaze. They tell her she needs to be stopped, but she refuses and lunges to attack only to be trapped in a pentagram.

Strange casts a spell that separates the spirit from Barb's body, but before he can trap it Blaze breaks the pentagram to tend to Barb and sets it free to possess someone else. The heroes gather around Barb who dies from the exertion of the separation, saying it's better for everyone that way.
name: What If Barbara Ketch Had Become Ghost Rider?

description:
This is the story of Skywise's birth and his father Shale's death. Skywise' mom while pregnant climbed to the top of a tall pine and looked at the clear stars for nights on end, pretending to speak to Skywise.
This story is set before ElfQuest the original series. Skywise and Brownberry are lovers who encounter upon a human named "Taf" who murdered Shale. This is what happened:
Taf and his brother had seen Skywise' mom for many nights climb the same tree and wait in the birds nest on top. They decided to wait for her one night, and when they found her, Shale arrived to see the brothers stone his wife. She fell out of the tree, and gave birth soon thereafter. Shale was killed on the group, and his wife died shortly after giving birth to Skywise.
This retroactively explains why, in the original Quest, we see a history for Skywise which would make his hatred and mistrust of humans sensible. Thus, he could not believe when Cutter stood before humans in peace in ElfQuest #12.
name: STARFALL, STARRISE

description:
Xavier, Cyclops, and Jean Grey help Wolverine work out his memories in the Danger Room. Wolverine relives Sabretooth killing Silver Fox. Sabretooth brings up Wolverine killing Terry Adams. Wolverine tells the X-Men that he was assigned another mission.

Wolverine cools off at a bar. Wolverine picks a fight to numb the pain of Silver Fox and loses an eye. Jean Grey comes to the bar and talks to Logan.

Nick Fury and John Wraith take Logan to the “cabin” where they will bury Silver Fox.

Homage cover: to X-Men #138.
name: State Of Grace!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Batman takes a wrong turn into an abandoned movie studio and falls prey to a creature of the night more fearsome than himself. It's up to Alfred, fearless vampire hunter, to save his master from the curse of the undead in "Sunset." This 1-issue special is from the creative team of SCARLETT (see Scarlett (1993)).
name: Sunset

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Before he was Drax the Destroyer, Guardian of the Galaxy, he was Arthur Douglas, a mediocre jazz musician and all-around family man. Drax travels to the deserts of Nevada after recalling his human death. The past comes flooding in, providing many painful memories for Drax and Moondragon.
name: Distant Memories

description:
Even as Laurel Kennedy and Heath preside over the official mourning of the heir to the Khan, young Jupiter Assante and his captor are indeed alive and, well... on the run. Beneath a strangely deserted and overgrown castle, Grendel and Jupiter are set upon by a group of mutated casualties of the nuclear winter, a group carrying a decided grudge against manipulators of modern technology. A mysterious band of soldiers arrives in time to add another surprising twist to the story. For our heroes, it's a case of out of the frying pan and into the fires of the "Devil in Hell"!

Grendel Prime and Jupiter travel to the wasteland left from a nuclear winter. They stop at a ruined building to gather fresh water to continue their journey. A cloaked figure from the shadows draws Jupiter from the bike into the underground depths. There he was almost captured by a band of mutants before Grendel Prime showd up to save him. The child was protected by a radiation suit, but Grendel was growing increasingly weak due to the radiation levels. Prime and Jupiter were captured by mutants who blamed technology for all of their problems. Prime and Jupiter narrowly escaped when a group of armed persons in radiation suits rescued them and took them captive.

This issue also includes a recap of the "Incubation Years," when the Grendel spirit inhabited Captain Wiggins and then spread out to become an abstract cultural force.
name: Devil in Hell

description: Torn between almost a dozen nigh-omnipotent mystical entities seeking to recruit him for the coming War of the Seven Spheres, Doctor Strange must make the ultimate sacrifice to escape a life of abject servitude.
name: The Wrath of Gods

description:
1. Women 4

The Cirinists watch Cerebus carefully as he sleepwalks with his sword raised and him dreaming. The Tower gets bigger and part of the Regency Hotel is crushed. Cerebus lowers his sword, and rests from his sleepwalk on a stairway.

  1. Address to the Diamond Seminar (6/14/ 92)

Dave talks about the comic book industry

  1. Don't You Want Me (a preview by Lee Carey and Desmond Lagan)
name: Mothers and Daughters 16 : Women 4

description:
The epic battle between Superman and Doomsday continues as Doomsday reaches Metropolis! Can Superman stop Doomsday from destroying the city he calls home?

Doomsday finally gets to Metropolis despite Superman and other heroes' best efforts. Doomsday takes on everything Metropolis has to offer. He takes on Cadmus, the Guardian, the Underworlders, Team Luthor, Metropolis Special Crimes Unit and even Emil Hamilton and a special ray gun. Doomsday looks unfazed and Superman is on the ropes.

Notes:

  • Triangle 1993 #1.
  • Each page consists of two panels.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #684.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #75.
name: Doomsday is Here!

description:
Classic Judge Dredd reprints from the pages of weekly British anthology comic 2000AD.

Cover: Brian Williamson (Judge Dredd)

  • The Stookie Glanders (progs 220-221) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Ian Gibson)
  • Mob Wars (progs 222-223) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Ron Smith)
  • Diary of a Mad Citizen (progs 229-230) (John Wagner and Alan Grant - Colin Wilson)
name: Judge Dredd 76

description:
Classic Judge Dredd reprints from the pages of weekly British anthology comic 2000AD.

Cover: Sean Phillips (Judge Dredd)

  • Young Giant (progs 651-655) (John Wagner - Carlos Ezquerra)
name: Dredd Rules! 17

description: King Snake makes his moves on KGBeast's territory and Tim confronts new difficulties with his father.
name: Dosvedanya, Baby

volume.name: Robin III: Cry of the Huntress

description: The Punisher's harassment of the Kingpin finally overrides the amusement value of hiding the man the Punisher wants to kill. The criminal is thrown to Frank Castle, who executes him via train. This does not calm the ghosts.
Wolverine and Venom join forces against the evil Nightmare.
name: Claws and Webs part 6 of 6: Nightmare's End

description:
After the explosion of last issue, Black Condor is rushed to the hospital. Ned Smith and Bonnie Robinson arrive and recap for the police the events leading to the explosion. However, the explanation is cut short when the Black Condor is transformed into this mute, rocky, gargoyle-like creature. The gargoyle-Condor flees the hospital.
 
Meanwhile, the lava creature from Black Condor #7 slips into Philadelphia, intent to attack the Solarchem headquarters. The lava creature attacks, which draws the attention of Happy Terrill. Happy and his son Ray Terrill, the first and second Ray, head out to stop the creature, but the gargoyle-Condor arrives first. The gargoyle-Condor, with only animal-like intelligence, attacks the lava creature.
 
The gargoyle-Condor and the lava creature are soon both attacked by the two Rays. When gargoyle-Condor tries to save Ned Smith, Ray Terrill mistakenly thinks it is an attack, and fries gargoyle-Condor. When the smoke clears, everyone thinks that gargoyle-Condor is destroyed… until the gargoyle-Condor rises from the crater double in size.
name: Where Monsters Walk!

description: Terror is hired by a man sentenced to the electric chair. He wants the protaganist to use his body parts to give his family one last Christmas with 'him'. Organized crime decides to take revenge on the man for past indiscretions by going after his innocent family. Terror ends up fighting the Maggia in order to save the man's wife and son. Then he uses the man's hands to give the sleeping wife one last moment of comfort, the disembodied hand makes the woman recall pleasing memories of their marriage.
name: The Gift of the Maggia

description:
In this corner - Archer and Armstrong! In the other - a room full of viscous Sect members! It's the brawl to end all brawls, as Archer and Armstrong find themselves trapped in an ominous castle with no way out. With ancient secrets and fists lurking around every corner, Archer and Armstrong are in for a bloody good time.

Continuing their romp across Europe, Archer and Armstrong run out of gas near a French chateau. Knocking for help, they discover that the mansion houses a Sect smuggling ring! Mayhem ensues as the mighty Armstrong enjoys a brawl with the criminals. But when the bad guys whip out a rocket-launcher, Archer's kung fu puts a quick end to the smugglers -- and to Armstrong's play time.

A man with no name on the run from the mafia and the sinister Japanese conglomerate, Iwatsu Industries, Bloodshot will stop at nothing to learn the secret of his nanite-fueled second life.

A criminal/terrorist operation is suddenly shattered by a vigilante with burning eyes and a crimson disc upon his chest. Bloodshot has arrived! Soon, a pair of inhuman manhunters are dispatched to bring Bloodshot back to the lab where they all were spawned. But the synthetic blood in these "Speedshots" is a pale imitation of the Blood of Heroes in Bloodshot's veins, and the nanite-enhanced hero prevails!

First appearances:

- Sinclaire (Para-Man II)

- Benito Carboni

- Iwatsu

- Malcolm

Bloodshot 1 is a very rare volume, due to it's release date. It was released the very same day as The Death of Superman.
name: Blood Of The Machine

description:
Throughout his many centuries on Earth, Gilad has made countless enemies, but few friends. Now, as Master Darque's war against the Geomancers continues, Gilad must say goodbye to a very old friend.

Years ago, Geomancer Buck McHenry saved the life of the Eternal Warrior. Now, Gilad finds that he must kill his friend Buck, or risk evil Master Darque using the knowledge of the Geomancers for his own ends. After slaying Buck with the soul-stealing knife, teh Bagh-Nakh, Gilad must fight Darque for possession of the weapon. The blade is shattered, releasing mystic forces that nearly destroy both Gilad and Darque!
name: Space & Time

description:
Tensions run high when the team starts breaking in Maniac's new replacement. Flatline's first day back to life in the H.A.R.D. Corps may just be his last when things go disastrously wrong during his first live fire exercise.

Going about their private lives, Gunslinger, Hammerhead, Shakespeare, and Superstar are called back to the H.A.R.D. Corps base to meet their newest rookie, Sam Yoon Kim. Sam joins the others on a training exercise through a deadly obstacle course, where he shows more concern for his teammates than for completing the mission. With a begrudging welcome, they christen their new teammate "Flatline."
name: Slaughter Street

description:
It's a psychological journey into the mind of Zeypher! As Faith's relationship with Peter Stanchek sours, she experiences a string of mysterious dreams. What do these visions means for Zephyr and how will they affect her in reality? Also, Toyo Harada has startling news for one of his students!

Kris is plagued by nightmares about the fate of the baby she gave up during the Unity conflict. So preoccupied is she by the loss of the child, that the others are beginning to fear for her mental health. At last, Pete secretly enters Kris' sleeping mind to give her recurring nightmares a happier ending. Realizing that she must let the child go to pursue his destiny as Magnus, Kris finally is able to get on with the rest of her life.

1st Appearance:

  • Stronghold (Edward T. Sedgwick)
name: Dream Child

description:
Magnus returns to the asylum that 1-A created on Phobos and discovers that things have changed and not for the better and that a new version of an old threat is going to invade Earth in “Armageddon 4002 Part One – Slaughter on Phobos.”

Arriving at the Asylum on Phobos, Magnus discovers that powerful, new robots have taken over and murdered the inmates. Only Izak survives to learn with Magnus that these are robots from Malev-6, out to conquer Earth in retaliation for Magnus's destruction of their own robot planet. Captured by the Malev Emperor, Magnus must watch helplessly as the evil robots launch their all-out invasion of North Am!

Variant Cover: Gold Logo (see cover below).

1st. appearances:

- Malevolents

- Malev Emperor
name: Armageddon 4002 Part 1: Slaughter On Phobos!

description:
After months of preparation, Darque rules the night! A sadistic soul-eater, Master Darque has come gunning for Jack Boniface — with an offer he can't refuse! Will Jack make a deal with the devil, or will New Orleans burn under Darque's spell? Plus, an old enemy returns from the grave!

Contemplating his nightly appetite for violence, Jack begins to feel that Shadowman is a seperate personality within himself. But Jack hasn't long to wonder as he is attacked by one of Master Darque's zombies. Taken captive, Jack is brought before Master Darque, who offers him his heart's desire if he will serve him. When Jack refuses, Darque leaves him to battle the savage zombie while the house burns down around them!

1st appearance:

- Sandria Darque, Sister of Master Darque

Death of Marty.
name: Darque

description: Back from the Spider Alien Moonbase, Phil recalls that before he destroyed the world, he had averted some imminent nuclear disasters. But the infamy he gained fixing those plants contributed to the horrifying downfall. So, this time around, he surreptitiously gets the plant personnel to notice the reactor leaks themselves, with no one the wiser that they were saved by the Man of the Atom!
name: Critical Mess

description:
It's the finale to "The Seeds of Destruction" saga! Aric and Maka will fight to the death-- on the moon! But without the aid of the X-O armor, what chance does Aric have against a killer with blood colder than space? One will fall and one will claim the prize: the seed of Shanhara!

Within the moonbase, Aric goes toe-to-toe with the hulking Spider Champion! The alien anticipates an easy victory, only to find that, even without the Armor, Aric still has the strength to snap his neck! When Solar is unable to find out the Spider Homeworld's location, only one option remains: obliteraiton of the alien moonbase. So, reclaiming the Armor, Aric leaves Solar, who first destroys the base, then vaporizes the Spore!
name: The Darkside To Victory

description:
Variant cover: Platinum version (see below)

A Predator stalks North Am 4001, searching for his most prized trophy -- the X-O Manowar helmet. The stolen trophy has fallen into the hands of a certain Goph, a man called Magnus, whose steel-mashing strength has earned him the title Robot Fighter -- thus the stage is set for the battle of the 41st century!
name: Part One: Sport

description:
Will Sir Woodworth and his cohorts enjoy inconceivable riches or face complete devastation? Don't miss the exciting final chapter and epilogue of "In Search of Peter Pan"! Impatient for transformation, Shamah gets far more than he expects in chapter four of "Rork: Starlight," and Phil Elliott strikes a note of cautious paranoia in "Conspiracy Theory."

Story Titles

  • Conspiracy Theory
  • In Search of Peter Pan Chapter 9
  • Rork: Starlight Chapter 4

Overview

Leia, Luke, Han, and Chewie make it out of Doctor Arakkus' death trap by the skin of their teeth and head for home at long last -- only to discover that Rebel headquarters is under Imperial attack! Will they find safe haven with new allies on the water world of Aquaris, or will those allies turn out to be as dangerous as Darth Vader?
name: Deadly Reunion (part 2), Traitor's Gambit (part 1)

description:
Meet Cross: outlaw, freelance avenger, and, when the situation calls for it, professional killer. He's just the kind of person the Predators might take an interest in -- which is why the government's Predator Task Force wants him! Next month Predator: Race War debuts as a four-issue color miniseries. Story by novelist Andrew Vachss (Hard Looks), adapted by Randy Stradley (Aliens vs. Predator) and artists Jordan Raskin and John Beatty (Punisher). Also: Jo Duffy and Maya Sakamoto's Nestrobber preview concludes, and the heroine of Gary Davis' "Paleolove" seeks a love potion from Mudwike, the dwarf. Painted cover by Ray Lago (Hellraiser).

Chapters

  • Predator: Race War - Part 3 (of 3)
  • Nestrobber: "Survival Skills"
  • Paleolove - Part 2
  • Alec - "An Old Australian Yarn"
name: Predator; Nestrobber; Paleolove; Alec

description:
Part 5 of the 8-part 'Funeral for a Friend,': Brooding over the death of his greatest obstruction, Superman, Lex Luthor becomes paranoid that Superman is pulling the same hoax on the world as Luthor did - faking his own death!

Notes:

  • Triangle 1993 #7.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #76.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #686.
name: Funeral for a Friend, Part 5: Grave Obsession

description: "Flesh and Blood Part 6: Incarnate" and "Flesh and Blood Part 7: Metamorphosis" This giant-sized issue concludes the ground breaking 'Flesh and Blood' storyline as Animal Man attempts to regain his lost humanity and Cliff struggles to survive Uncle Dudley's cave of death.
name: Flesh and Blood, Part Six: Incarnate; Part Seven: Metamorphosis

description: Bruce Wayne is exhausted! But there's no rest for the weary! A delusional Killer Croc is causing havoc in the slums of Gotham's homeless community. In order to keep up appearances, Tim Drake convinces Jean-Paul Valley to dress as Batman in Bruce's absence and head to the scene. Meanwhile Killer Croc has also caught the eye of Bane. He decides to take the Killer Croc out of the equation while hoping to run into Batman along the way. Jean-Paul mistakenly turns his back on Croc during their battle and is beaten by Killer Croc. Bane then dispatches Croc and afterward he realizes that this isn't the Batman he was hoping for.
name: Killer's Bane

description: Continuing the story from Issue Number 4, The Dynamic Duo find out that the Scarecrow is the one that has robbed Gotham City. Now they have to find a way to stop him Even Professor Crane has doubts about what he is doing, and questions how a man who has dedicated his life to education continue with a plan like this.
name: Riot Act II

description: Congo Bill returns to his weakened, aging body...in time to battle alone against the brute strength and cunning of the Golden Gorilla.
name: I Pray the Lord My Soul to Take...

description: The Gordons, the Creeper and Cave Carson try to infiltrate Eclipso's country from below. Cave has his legs broken and is left on the border. The Gordons are taken on a tour of the horrors Eclipso has visited upon the country.
name: The Wings of Vengeance!

description: "One Perfect Gift." Wally West and Linda Park spend Christmas with the Garricks. While dinner is being prepared, Wally and Jay Garrick, the original Flash, head out into the snowy weather to run, talk, and spread a little Christmas cheer.
name: One Perfect Gift

description: It was an age of change, a time when a new awareness was spreading across America, a sense that people mattered and weren't powerless against corporate and political corruption. Into this brave new world came a hero for the times, one who evoked a medieval legend of another movement to 'fight the power.' GREEN ARROW: THE WONDER YEAR tells the story of the earliest days of the Emerald Archer's career as a true hero of the common man. Like the mythical Robin Hood, Green Arrow is a hero forced into existence by the challenges of the world around him - a world rife with greed and injustice. What were the influences that shaped the character of Oliver Queen, the events that evolved him from a careless corporate boor into a streetwise, hard-edged vigilante? The tale is told here!
name: The Wonder Year Part 1

description: Christmas Issue. "The Ghost of Christmas Light!". In this special Holiday issue, Hal brings Carol home to meet his folks. However, the Yule Tide spirit may be dimmed when the nefarious Doctor Light shows up seeking Green Lantern's power source.
name: The Ghost of Christmas Light

description: Christmas on the Mosaic. Or is it Hanukkah? Or is it the Xudarian festival of Tuxushta? The Sweet-smoke-night of the Berserkers? Or the Steam Frogs'...well...different cultures have different customs. Suffice it to say a holiday party at John Stewart's place is an event most decidedly not to be missed.
name: Merry Mosaic

description: Flight's End, Part 5 of 6. Someone's supplying the Netherworld with the deadly, lycanthropic drug 'Hairballs,' and Katar and Shayera set out to find the source and cut it off. But Count Viper has other plans for the Hawks - plans that will ultimately bring their whole world crashing down!
name: Flight's End, Part 5: Trash
